<TITLE> BDR man dies of heart attack </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Sep 23 (bdnews24.com)--A border guard died of a heart attack at Dhaka Medical College Hospital on Tuesday night, the BDR said in a press release. Mohammed Amzad Hossain, 45, hhabilder of 19 Rifles Battalion in Comilla was admitted to the BDR hospital as he was suffering from diabetes and heart disease. He was then moved to DMCH on Sep 12 as his condition did not improve. He has a wife, two sons and a daughter and he will be buried at his village at Tarpurchandi of Baburhat in Chandpur. 
